A.2 Stochastic Calculus

· Itô's lemma: $df(\Xi) = \frac{\partial f}{\partial \Xi^\mu} d\Xi^\mu + \frac12 \frac{\partial^2 f}{\partial \Xi^\mu \partial \Xi^\nu} d\Xi^\mu d\Xi^\nu$.
· Generator of a diffusion: $\mathcal{L} = f^\mu \partial_\mu + \frac12 (\sigma \sigma^T)^{\mu\nu} \partial_\mu \partial_\nu$.

A.3 Viscosity Solutions of HJI Equations

A continuous function $V$ is a viscosity solution of $H(\Xi, \nabla V) = 0$ if for any smooth test function $\phi$ touching $V$ from above (resp. below) at $\Xi$, we have $H(\Xi, \nabla \phi(\Xi)) \le 0$ (resp. $\ge 0$).

