B.2 Proof of Theorem 6.1 (Collapse Threshold)

Sketch. By assumption, the dynamics near the critical point reduce to the B‑T normal form. The homoclinic bifurcation curve is given by $\mu_1 = -\frac{6}{25}\mu_2^2 + O(\mu_2^3)$ (Kuznetsov 2004). Substituting the expressions for $\mu_1, \mu_2$ in terms of physical parameters and solving for $\text{Mk} = 1$ yields the threshold. Details are lengthy but follow standard bifurcation analysis.

B.3 Proof of Proposition 10.1 (Geodesic Principle)

The entropy production along a path $\gamma$ is $\Delta \Sigma = \int_\gamma \sqrt{g_{\mu\nu}^{\text{eff}} \dot{\Xi}^\mu \dot{\Xi}^\nu} dt$. Minimizing this action functional leads to the Euler‑Lagrange equations, which are equivalent to the geodesic equation in the metric $g^{\text{eff}}$.

